
[1]detail

   DETAIL, v.t.

   1. To relate, report or narrate in particulars; to recite the
   particulars of; to particularize; to relate minutely and distinctly;
   as, he detailed all the facts in due order.

   2. To select, as an officer or soldier from a division, brigade,
   regiment or battalion.

                                 DETAIL, n.

   1. A narration or report of particulars; a minute and particular
   account. He related the story in detail. He gave a detail of all the
   transactions.

   2. A selecting of officer or soldiers from the rosters.
